		<title>01Gazeteer</title>
		<content> Llandrindod Wells is the county town  
 of Powys situated in the Ithon Valley,
 230 metres above sea level.The 1981   
 census showed that the population of  
 the town was just under 4,500.Besides 
 being an administrative centre,the    
 town is famous as a spa and attracts a
 considerable number of tourists during
 the season.                           
  Howey is a village situated two miles
 south of Llandrindod well-protected in
 a hollow.It has a population of about 
 300.                                  
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
